# 3 Reasons why programmers use documentation 
#1 Understanding documentation can help programmers understand the purpose of the code that they're about to use
#2 Documentation can help with collabing on projects i can help keep people on the same page.
# 3 Troubleshooting documentation can aide with the Troubleshooting process by offering insights on the code you're making

#if a programmer has bad or no documentation it could cause more errors. Without goog documentation havig a full understanding of the code becomes more challenging 
Bad/No documentation could aslo cause less colobaration and knowledge loss. i say this because documentation is a place where you store your knowledge about your code and also where you g to connect with collaborators.
